## M22: extern call wrapped in a `raw` block is allowed.
##
## The "safe wrapper" pattern around an FFI function: the
## public `safe_puts` Rig fn has a safe contract; internally
## it wraps the extern call in a `raw` block. Callers of
## `safe_puts` don't need to know about the FFI boundary.
##
## (Per GPT-5.5 entry 38: M22 intentionally lacks a Rust-style
## `unsafe sub`/`raw sub` precondition-marker. APIs with
## unchecked caller obligations are deferred until a future
## trusted/raw-function design pass forced by a real use case.
## V1 raw blocks support safe wrappers over raw internals;
## they don't support exposing raw preconditions through the
## public API.)

extern puts: fn(String) Int

sub safe_puts(s: String)
  raw
    puts(s)        # OK: inside `raw` block

sub main()
  safe_puts("hi")  # OK: safe_puts has a safe contract
